# hindsight_sync_retain --bank_id documentation --content "# Graphify Quick Reference\n\n# Graphify Quick Reference\n\n## Most Useful Commands\n\n### Search & Query\n```bash\n# Find information about a topic\ngraphify query \"your search terms\" --budget 2000\n\n# Explain a specific concept\ngraphify explain \"component-name\"\n\n# Find relationship between two concepts\ngraphify path \"concept-A\" \"concept-B\"\n```\n\n### Maintenance\n```bash\n# Quick update after code changes (no LLM cost)\ngraphify update .\n\n# Check if graph needs updating\ngraphify check-update .\n\n# Full re-extraction with semantic analysis\ngraphify extract . --backend gemini\n```\n\n### Navigation\n```bash\n# View the graph report\ncat graphify-out/GRAPH_REPORT.md | less\n\n# Search within graph report\ngrep -i \"keyword\" graphify-out/GRAPH_REPORT.md\n```\n\n## Example Queries\n\n### Architecture Questions\n```bash\ngraphify query \"CollabMind architecture components\"\ngraphify query \"memory gateway design\"\ngraphify query \"authentication flow\"\n```\n\n### Code Navigation\n```bash\ngraphify query \"memory storage implementation\"\ngraphify query \"document indexing system\"\ngraphify query \"MCP server endpoints\"\n```\n\n### Documentation Search\n```bash\ngraphify query \"deployment guide\"\ngraphify query \"environment configuration\"\ngraphify query \"runbook procedures\"\n```\n\n## Understanding the Graph Structure\n\n- **876 communities** = algorithmically clustered groups of related concepts\n- **17,444 nodes** = code symbols, files, documentation sections\n- **32,069 edges** = relationships (93% extracted from code, 7% inferred by LLM)\n\n## Community Labels Explained\n\nLabels like \"Community 0\", \"Community 1\" are **expected behavior**:\n- Numeric IDs are assigned by clustering algorithm\n- To find meaningful content, use `graphify query` instead\n- Each community groups related concepts together\n\n## Tips for Best Results\n\n1. **Use broad keywords** in queries - the BFS traversal will find related nodes\n2. **Increase budget** if results seem incomplete: `--budget 3000`\n3. **Combine related terms**: \"memory vector storage\" finds more than \"memory\" alone\n4. **Us" --context documentation --tags "source:docs,type:documentation"

