# hindsight_sync_retain --bank_id documentation --content "# Gemini\n\n# GEMINI.md - CollabMind XAI-v2 Project Instructions\n\n## Project Overview\nCollabMind XAI-v2 is an **operator-first AI memory, knowledge, and identity control plane**. It acts as a governed gateway between agents/humans and various memory/retrieval engines. The core philosophy is that LLM models are replaceable, but the **governance, audit, and context-pack layers** are the project's primary moat.\n\n## Core Mandates\n1. **Governed Access Only:** No engine (OpenMemory, memlord, Graphiti, etc.) should be called directly by agents or users. All traffic MUST route through the **Central API** (`stacks/collabmind/api`).\n2. **Auth on Everything:** Every endpoint (except `/health`) requires authentication via Authentik OIDC (JWT) or an API Key (`X-Api-Key` or `Bearer mem11_sk_...`).\n3. **Internal Trust Chain:** `collabmind-api` verifies auth at the edge and injects a signed `X-CM-Context` (HMAC-SHA256) into internal hops. Downstream services trust this signed header.\n4. **Metadata First:** In retrieval tasks, metadata filters (tenant, status, confidentiality) MUST run before semantic vector searches. Semantic similarity alone is never an authority signal.\n\n## Project Structure\n- `stacks/collabmind/api`: **Central API (Node.js/Express)**. The primary governance edge and routing layer. Current working implementation.\n- `stacks/collabmind/central-api`: **Central API (Python/FastAPI)**. Contract-first scaffold for the future Python-based control plane.\n- `stacks/collabmind/mcp`: **MCP Gateway**. Exposes CollabMind tools to agents, routing all calls through the Central API.\n- `engines/`: Specialized retrieval engines (OpenMemory, memlord, coderag) that serve as pluggable backends.\n- `docs-old-ref/`: Historical documentation (use `README.md` and `stacks/collabmind/deploy/SERVICE_REGISTRY.md` for current state).\n- `graphify-out/`: Knowledge graph and analysis of the codebase.\n\n## Key Service Endpoints (Dev)\n- Central API: `http://localhost:3050`\n- Console UI: `http://localhost:3060`\n" --context documentation --tags "source:docs,type:documentation"

