# hindsight_sync_retain --bank_id documentation --content "# Agents\n\n## graphify\n\nThis project has a graphify knowledge graph at graphify-out/.\n\nRules:\n- Before answering architecture or codebase questions, read graphify-out/GRAPH_REPORT.md for god nodes and community structure\n- If graphify-out/wiki/index.md exists, navigate it instead of reading raw files\n- For cross-module \"how does X relate to Y\" questions, prefer `graphify query \"<question>\"`, `graphify path \"<A>\" \"<B>\"`, or `graphify explain \"<concept>\"` over grep — these traverse the graph's EXTRACTED + INFERRED edges instead of scanning files\n- After modifying code files in this session, run `graphify update .` to keep the graph current (AST-only, no API cost)\n\n## Memory Backend Migration\n\n**Primary Memory Engine:** Hindsight (read-write via MCP)\n- Bank: `collabmind-control-plane`\n- 15 active directives covering security, governance, testing, deployment\n- 8 mental models for architecture understanding\n- Full CRUD support via `HindsightAdapter` at `stacks/collabmind/central-api/app/adapters/hindsight.py`\n- Configuration: `CENTRAL_API_HINDSIGHT_URL`, `CENTRAL_API_HINDSIGHT_API_KEY`, `CENTRAL_API_HINDSIGHT_BANK_ID`\n\n**Legacy Memory Engine:** Memlord (read-only federation)\n- `MemlordAdapter.read_only = True`\n- Searches memlord but never writes to it\n- Used for backward compatibility during migration\n- Configuration: `CENTRAL_API_MEMLORD_URL`, `CENTRAL_API_MEMLORD_API_KEY`\n\n**Migration:** 594 memories migrated from memlord to hindsight with preserved:\n- memory_type (fact, preference, instruction, feedback, decision)\n- workspace tags\n- metadata\n- Migration script: `scripts/migrate-memlord-to-hindsight.ts`\n" --context documentation --tags "source:docs,type:documentation"

