# hindsight_sync_retain --bank_id documentation --content "# Browser Import Guide\n\n# Browser Import Guide (Easiest Method)\n\n**For:** http://localhost:7474  \n**Credentials:** neo4j / password\n\nSince finding the import directory can be tricky, here's the **easiest method** using Neo4j Browser directly.\n\n---\n\n## ✅ Method 1: Use Neo4j Browser File Upload (Recommended)\n\n### Step 1: Open Neo4j Browser\n\nGo to: **http://localhost:7474**\n\nLogin:\n- Username: `neo4j`\n- Password: `password`\n\n### Step 2: Upload CSV Files\n\nIn Neo4j Browser:\n\n1. Click the **document icon** (top left) to open the sidebar\n2. Click **Import** tab\n3. Drag and drop both CSV files:\n   - `nodes.csv` (5.0 MB)\n   - `relationships.csv` (10 MB)\n\nOr use the file picker to select them from:\n```\n/Users/oliververmeulen/XAI-v2/neo4j/\n```\n\n### Step 3: Create Constraints\n\nCopy and paste into Neo4j Browser:\n\n```cypher\n// Create constraints\nCREATE CONSTRAINT graphify_node_id IF NOT EXISTS \nFOR (n:GraphifyNode) REQUIRE n.id IS UNIQUE;\n\n// Create indexes\nCREATE INDEX graphify_label IF NOT EXISTS \nFOR (n:GraphifyNode) ON (n.label);\n\nCREATE INDEX graphify_community IF NOT EXISTS \nFOR (n:GraphifyNode) ON (n.community);\n\nCREATE INDEX graphify_source IF NOT EXISTS \nFOR (n:GraphifyNode) ON (n.source_file);\n```\n\n### Step 4: Import Nodes\n\n**IMPORTANT:** After uploading CSV files, they're accessible as `file:///nodes.csv`\n\n```cypher\n// Import nodes (takes 2-3 minutes)\nLOAD CSV WITH HEADERS FROM 'file:///nodes.csv' AS row\nCREATE (n:GraphifyNode {\n  id: row.`id:ID`,\n  label: row.label,\n  norm_label: row.norm_label,\n  file_type: row.file_type,\n  source_file: row.source_file,\n  source_location: row.source_location,\n  community: toInteger(row.`community:int`)\n})\nRETURN count(n) as nodes_created;\n```\n\n**Expected output:** nodes_created: 30,724\n\nIf you get an error about transactions, use this instead:\n\n```cypher\n:auto LOAD CSV WITH HEADERS FROM 'file:///nodes.csv' AS row\nCALL {\n  WITH row\n  CREATE (n:GraphifyNode {\n    id: row.`id:ID`,\n    label: row.label,\n    norm_label: row.norm_label,\n    file_type: row.file_ty" --context documentation --tags "source:docs,type:documentation"

