# hindsight_sync_retain --bank_id documentation --content "# How Graphify Works\n\n# How Graphify is Managed in XAI-v2\n\n## Overview\n\nGraphify is a knowledge graph tool that analyzes code repositories and creates queryable knowledge graphs. It's installed and actively used in the XAI-v2 project to understand the codebase structure.\n\n## Installation\n\n**Method**: Installed via `uv` (Python package manager)\n\n```bash\n# Installed as a uv tool\nuv tool install graphifyy\n\n# Location\n~/.local/bin/graphify -> ~/.local/share/uv/tools/graphifyy/bin/graphify\n```\n\n**Version**: \n- CLI version: v0.7.9\n- Package version: 0.4.23\n\n**Package Info**:\n- PyPI package: `graphifyy`\n- GitHub: https://github.com/safishamsi/graphify\n- License: MIT\n\n## Current Graph State\n\nThe XAI-v2 project has an active knowledge graph at `/Users/oliververmeulen/XAI-v2/graphify-out/`:\n\n```\ngraphify-out/\n├── graph.json              # Main graph data (31.9 MB)\n├── GRAPH_REPORT.md         # Human-readable report (390 KB)\n├── manifest.json           # Graph metadata (547 KB)\n├── .graphify_analysis.json # Analysis cache (948 KB)\n├── .graphify_labels.json   # Label mappings (20 KB)\n├── .graphify_root          # Root path marker\n└── cache/                  # Build cache\n```\n\n## Graph Statistics\n\n- **30,932 nodes** (code symbols, files, documentation)\n- **59,204 edges** (relationships between nodes)\n- **1,546 communities** (algorithmically clustered groups)\n- **2,903 files** analyzed (~2.3M words)\n- **93% EXTRACTED** edges (direct from code)\n- **7% INFERRED** edges (AI-inferred relationships)\n\n## How It Works\n\n### 1. Code Analysis\nGraphify uses tree-sitter parsers to extract:\n- Functions, classes, methods\n- Imports and dependencies\n- File structure\n- Documentation\n\n### 2. Relationship Extraction\n- **EXTRACTED**: Direct relationships from code (imports, calls, contains)\n- **INFERRED**: AI-inferred semantic relationships (uses, rationale_for, etc.)\n\n### 3. Community Detection\nGroups related nodes into communities using graph algorithms (Leiden/Louvain clustering).\n\n### 4. Output Formats\n- **graph.json" --context documentation --tags "source:docs,type:documentation"

