# hindsight_sync_retain --bank_id documentation --content "# Import To Existing\n\n# Import Graphify Data to Existing Neo4j\n\n**Target:** http://localhost:7474  \n**Credentials:** neo4j / password\n\n---\n\n## Quick Import (Copy & Paste Method)\n\n### Step 1: Find Your Neo4j Import Directory\n\nYour Neo4j instance needs the CSV files in its `import` directory.\n\n**Find it:**\n- **Neo4j Desktop:** Settings → Open Folder → Import\n- **Mac Default:** `~/Library/Application Support/com.Neo4j.Relate/Data/dbmss/dbms-*/import/`\n- **Linux Default:** `~/.config/Neo4j Desktop/Application/relate-data/dbmss/dbms-*/import/`\n\n**Or query Neo4j:**\n```cypher\nCALL dbms.listConfig() \nYIELD name, value \nWHERE name = 'server.directories.import' \nRETURN value;\n```\n\n### Step 2: Copy CSV Files\n\nCopy these two files to your Neo4j import directory:\n```bash\n# Example (adjust path to your actual import directory):\ncp /Users/oliververmeulen/XAI-v2/neo4j/nodes.csv ~/Library/Application\ Support/com.Neo4j.Relate/Data/dbmss/dbms-*/import/\ncp /Users/oliververmeulen/XAI-v2/neo4j/relationships.csv ~/Library/Application\ Support/com.Neo4j.Relate/Data/dbmss/dbms-*/import/\n```\n\nOr use the finder script:\n```bash\n# Run this to find and copy automatically\ncd /Users/oliververmeulen/XAI-v2/neo4j\n./find-and-copy-csv.sh\n```\n\n### Step 3: Open Neo4j Browser\n\nGo to: http://localhost:7474\n\nLogin with:\n- Username: `neo4j`\n- Password: `password`\n\n### Step 4: Run Import Queries\n\nCopy and paste the following queries **one section at a time** into Neo4j Browser.\n\n---\n\n## Import Queries\n\n### A. Create Constraints (Run First)\n\n```cypher\nCREATE CONSTRAINT graphify_node_id IF NOT EXISTS \nFOR (n:GraphifyNode) REQUIRE n.id IS UNIQUE;\n\nCREATE CONSTRAINT graphify_code_id IF NOT EXISTS \nFOR (n:GraphifyCode) REQUIRE n.id IS UNIQUE;\n\nCREATE CONSTRAINT graphify_doc_id IF NOT EXISTS \nFOR (n:GraphifyDocument) REQUIRE n.id IS UNIQUE;\n```\n\n### B. Create Indexes\n\n```cypher\nCREATE INDEX graphify_node_label IF NOT EXISTS \nFOR (n:GraphifyNode) ON (n.label);\n\nCREATE INDEX graphify_node_community IF NOT EXISTS \nFOR (n:GraphifyNode) ON" --context documentation --tags "source:docs,type:documentation"

