# hindsight_sync_retain --bank_id documentation --content "# Changelog\n\n# Changelog — memory-gateway\n\nAll notable changes are documented here.  \nFormat follows [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.0.0/).  \nThis project uses [Semantic Versioning](https://semver.org/).\n\n---\n\n## [0.1.0] — 2026-05-29\n\n### Added\n\n- `GET /health` — unauthenticated liveness probe; returns service name, version, and active backend.\n- `GET /collections` — lists the configured collection/index for the active backend (no auth required).\n- `POST /remember` — accepts `{ title, content, metadata? }`, routes to active backend adapter, writes D1 audit row. Returns `{ ok, id, title, backend, collection_id }`.\n- `POST /search` — accepts `{ query, filters?, limit? }` (max 20), routes to active backend, returns `{ ok, backend, collection_id, query, filters_applied, count, results[] }`.\n- Dual backend architecture via `BACKEND_TYPE` env var:\n  - `vectorize` (default) — embeds content with `@cf/baai/bge-small-en-v1.5` via Workers AI, upserts vector to Cloudflare Vectorize, supports metadata filter object on search.\n  - `xai_collections` — pushes documents to xAI Collections API, searches via xAI Collections search endpoint, metadata-first filtering.\n- Four isolated adapter functions: `rememberVectorize`, `searchVectorize`, `rememberXaiCollection`, `searchXaiCollection`.\n- Cloudflare D1 `memory_registry` — immutable control plane for both backends; stores `id`, `title`, `collection_id`, `metadata_json`, `created_at`.\n- Optional bearer auth — if `GATEWAY_API_KEY` secret is set, all endpoints require `Authorization: Bearer <key>`; health and collections remain public.\n- Per-request `x-request-id` header on all responses.\n- TypeScript types (`src/types.ts`) — `MemoryMetadata`, `RememberRequest`, `SearchRequest`, `SearchResult`.\n\n### Design decisions\n\n- Backend is swappable without API contract change — identical request/response shape for both backends.\n- D1 is always the control plane regardless of backend; no semantic engine becomes authoritative for provenance.\n" --context documentation --tags "source:docs,type:documentation"

echo "  Importing: Readme..."
# hindsight_sync_retain --bank_id documentation --content "# Readme\n\n# Memory Gateway v0.1\n\n**Tiny, operator-controlled memory tool for agents.**\n\nCloudflare Worker acts as the neutral control layer (policy + metadata + routing + API contract).  \nSupports dual pluggable backends (`vectorize` default, `xai_collections`) via `BACKEND_TYPE` in wrangler.toml. D1 registry remains the immutable control plane for both (per xAI Collections RAG architecture: metadata filters first, independent provenance).\n\n## Core Design Principles\n\n- **Manual only** — Models/agents can only push what you explicitly allow via `/remember`.\n- **Metadata first** — Filters always applied before semantic search (cardinal rule from xAI Collections architecture).\n- **Backend is swappable** — `BACKEND_TYPE=vectorize|xai_collections`; D1 registry is control plane for both; adapters isolated as rememberXaiCollection/searchXaiCollection/rememberVectorize/searchVectorize.\n- **No autonomous memory** — No self-writing, no lifelong ingestion, no agent brain.\n- **Tiny surface** — Four endpoints maximum in v0.1.\n\n## Endpoints\n\n| Method | Path            | Purpose                              | Auth |\n|--------|-----------------|--------------------------------------|------|\n| GET    | `/health`       | Liveness + version                   | No   |\n| GET    | `/collections`  | List configured backends/collections | No   |\n| POST   | `/remember`     | Manually push content + metadata     | Optional |\n| POST   | `/search`       | Filtered semantic search             | Optional |\n\n## Configuration\n\nSet `BACKEND_TYPE=vectorize` (default) or `xai_collections` in `wrangler.toml` under `[vars]`. D1 always used as control plane. Switch is reversible.\n\n## Example Usage\n\n### Remember (push) - Vectorize (default)\n\n```bash\ncurl -X POST https://memory-gateway.yourdomain.workers.dev/remember \\n  -H \"content-type: application/json\" \\n  -H \"authorization: Bearer \$GATEWAY_API_KEY\" \\