# hindsight_sync_retain --bank_id documentation --content "# Backup Restore\n\n# Backup & Restore Procedures\n\n**Last Updated**: 2026-06-14  \n**Scope**: CollabMind data recovery and disaster recovery\n\n---\n\n## Quick Reference\n\n| Operation | Command | Time | Risk |\n|-----------|---------|------|------|\n| **Backup Postgres** | `pg_dump ... \| gzip > backup.sql.gz` | 1-5 min | Low |\n| **Restore Postgres** | `gunzip < backup.sql.gz \| psql ...` | 1-10 min | Medium (overwrites) |\n| **Backup Qdrant** | `curl .../snapshots -o snapshot.tar` | 1-2 min | Low |\n| **Restore Qdrant** | `curl -X PUT .../recover -F snapshot.tar` | 2-5 min | Medium |\n\n---\n\n## 1. Postgres Database Backup\n\n### Full Backup (All Data + Schema)\n\n#### Local Docker Container\n```bash\n#!/bin/bash\n# backup-postgres-docker.sh\n\nBACKUP_DIR=\"./backups\"\nTIMESTAMP=\$(date +%Y%m%d-%H%M%S)\nBACKUP_FILE=\"\$BACKUP_DIR/postgres-\$TIMESTAMP.sql.gz\"\n\nmkdir -p \"\$BACKUP_DIR\"\n\necho \"Starting Postgres backup...\"\ndocker exec collabmind-postgres pg_dump -U dev -d collabmind | gzip > \"\$BACKUP_FILE\"\n\nif [ \$? -eq 0 ]; then\n  SIZE=\$(du -h \"\$BACKUP_FILE\" | cut -f1)\n  echo \"✓ Backup complete: \$BACKUP_FILE (\$SIZE)\"\n  \n  # Keep only last 30 days\n  find \"\$BACKUP_DIR\" -name \"postgres-*.sql.gz\" -mtime +30 -delete\nelse\n  echo \"✗ Backup failed\"\n  exit 1\nfi\n```\n\n#### Remote Postgres Server\n```bash\n#!/bin/bash\n# backup-postgres-remote.sh\n\nBACKUP_DIR=\"./backups\"\nTIMESTAMP=\$(date +%Y%m%d-%H%M%S)\nBACKUP_FILE=\"\$BACKUP_DIR/postgres-\$TIMESTAMP.sql.gz\"\n\nmkdir -p \"\$BACKUP_DIR\"\n\necho \"Starting Postgres backup (remote)...\"\npg_dump -U postgres_user -h postgres.yourdomain.com -d collabmind \\n  --ssl-mode=require | gzip > \"\$BACKUP_FILE\"\n\nif [ \$? -eq 0 ]; then\n  SIZE=\$(du -h \"\$BACKUP_FILE\" | cut -f1)\n  echo \"✓ Backup complete: \$BACKUP_FILE (\$SIZE)\"\n  \n  # Keep only last 30 days\n  find \"\$BACKUP_DIR\" -name \"postgres-*.sql.gz\" -mtime +30 -delete\nelse\n  echo \"✗ Backup failed\"\n  exit 1\nfi\n```\n\n### Verification\n\n```bash\n# Check backup file size (should be > 1 MB for real data)\ndu -h backup-20260614-120000.sql.gz\n\n# List backup contents (without" --context documentation --tags "source:docs,type:documentation"

